nown for his contributions to he dicussion about currency systems and monetary policy in the government of British India, which was at the time exploring ways to achieve stabilization of the rupee. Both the arguments and the wealth of data in the reprint of this very rare book will be of interest to historians of Southeast Asia.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Economic History.2bisacsh1 aEng, Pierre van der, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Archive (pre 2000) eBook Packagez978311064968008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Archive eBook-Package 1970-1999z978311060669040uhttps://doi.org/10.1355/978981437946540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789814379465423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789814379465.jpg  a978-3-11-060669-0  ISEAS Archive eBook-Package 1970-1999c1970d1999  a978-3-11-064968-0  Asian Studies Archive (pre 2000) eBook Package  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK